        ## Behavior

        Grid does not have an opinion on the size of the individual columns within a page,
        but provides prescribed gap values (sometimes referred to as “gutter
        values”) to allow columns to scale on a percent-basis.

        {# `eds_figure` macro not used here intentionally #}
        
        <img src="/images/grid/Fluidity_optimized_800.gif" 
            class="docsite-animation-image"
            alt="Animated demonstration of breakpoints">
        
        For page widths up to 511px:
        -   Gap between columns is 12px (.75rem).
        -   Padding on the left and right of the `.eds-grid-root` is 16px (1rem).
        -   Column widths scale responsively maintaining consistent gap and
            padding values.

        For page widths of 512px to 1279px:
        -   Gap between columns is 24px (1.5rem).
        -   Padding on the left and right of the `.eds-grid-root` is 32px (2rem).
        -   Column widths scale responsively maintaining consistent gap and
            padding values.

        For page widths of 1280px and larger:
        -   Gap between columns is 24px (1.5rem).
        -   Padding no longer applies.
        -   Columns no longer scale.
        -   Page contents will center as page-background scales outward equally.

        Gap spacing applies between columns,
        not between elements within composed components, like the [Field Group](/components/field-group/field-group.html)
        or the [Content Block](/components/content-block/content-block.html). Neither the grid nor any row
        spacing will affect the contents of group-components. Refer to
        individual component documentation for inter-component space values.

        ## Vertical spacing

        No opinion is built into the eds Grid on the number of rows a page may
        have, but it's recommended that a 12px (.75rem) gap for `default`
        viewports and 24px (1.5rem) gap for `at-512` viewports be maintained
        between rows to match the space model of the columns. If you need
        alternative space values, it’s recommended you refer to the [Space
        Tokens](/visual-style/space/space.html).

        {% endfilter %}

