    ## Installation

    {% include "src/templates/partials/integration.njk" %}
    

    ## CSS block classes

    | Class name       | Applies to                                                      | Outcome                                                                                                                                                                  |
    | ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
    | `.eds-grid-root` | Any `block` display element you want to establish as a grid.     | Applies a max-width of 80rem (1280px) and adds predefined padding that adjusts from 1rem (16px) for the `default` breakpoint to 2rem (32px) for the `at-512` breakpoint. |


    ## CSS element classes

    | Class name        | Applies to                                                            | Outcome                                                                                                                                                                |
    | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    | `.eds-grid__grid` | Any block display type element you want to establish as a grid layout. | Applies CSS `display: grid;` with 12 explicit grid columns and a grid-gap width of .75rem (12px)/1.5rem (24px), `default`/`at-512`, respectively. |
    | `.eds-grid__item` | Any block display type element you want to use as a grid item.         | Applies a default column span                                                                                                             |

    ## CSS modifier classes

    The breakpoints available for use with the classes noted below are 512, 768, 960, and 1280.

    | Class name                                          | Applies to       | Outcome                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
    | --------------------------------------------------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    | `.eds-grid--disable-padding`                        | `.eds-grid-root`  | Removes default padding from the top-level grid container.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
    | `.eds-grid--disable-max-width`                      | `.eds-grid-root`  | Removes default max-width from the top-level grid container.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
    | `.eds-grid__item--default-column-span-[1-12]`       | `.eds-grid__grid` | Sets the default column span for all child `.eds-grid__item` elements to a given column span that do not have item modifier classes.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
    | `.eds-grid__item--column-span-[1-12]`               | `.eds-grid__item` | Sets the column span to 1-12 columns for an individual grid item. This sets the default column span across all breakpoints when breakpoint specific modifier classes are not present.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
    | `.eds-grid__item--column-span-[1-12]-[breakpoint]`  | `.eds-grid__item` | Sets the column span to a given number at a screen width of a given `breakpoint` and above. This will override the `.eds-grid__item--column-span-[1-12]` class when the `breakpoint` applies. Accepted breakpoint values available via [Design tokens](/visual-style/design-tokens/design-tokens.html?tab=current-tokens#breakpoints).                                                                                                                                                               |
    | `.eds-grid__item--column-start-[1-12]`              | `.eds-grid__item` | Sets the css value of `grid-column-start` for a grid item. Accepted `start` values range from 1-12 corresponding to the column where the grid item should start. This class is needed in addition to `.eds-grid__item--offset-[1-12]` for cross browser support.                                                                                                                                                                               |
    | `.eds-grid__item--column-start-[1-12]-[breakpoint]` | `.eds-grid__item` | Sets the css value of `grid-column-start` for a grid item at a given `breakpoint`. Accepted `start` values range from 1-12 corresponding to the column where the grid item should start. Accepted breakpoint values available via [Design tokens](/visual-style/design-tokens/design-tokens.html?tab=current-tokens#breakpoints). This class is needed in addition to `.eds-grid__item--offset-[1-12]-[breakpoint]` for cross browser support. |
    | `.eds-grid__item--row-span-[1-12]`                  | `.eds-grid__item` | Applies a given row span across all breakpoints. Accepted span values range from 1-12.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
    | `.eds-grid__item--row-span-[1-12]-[breakpoint]`     | `.eds-grid__item` | Applies a given row span at a given breakpoint. Accepted span values range from 1-12.  Accepted breakpoint values available via [Design tokens](/visual-style/design-tokens/design-tokens.html?tab=current-tokens#breakpoints).                                                                                                                                                                                                                |

    {% endfilter %}

